				<h1 class="txt-f4 txt-s7 balance-text">Refugees may become victims of Malaysia’s electoral politics</h1>
			</div>
			<div class="article-author pv-md col-sm-offset-3 col-sm-6">
															<a class="txt-dn txt-f1 txt-s3 txt-tu" href="/the-interpreter/contributors/articles/max-walden">
							Max Walden
						</a>
												</div>
							<div class="article-summary col-sm-offset-1 col-sm-10">
					<p class="txt-s5 txt-f1 balance-text txt-lmd">
						The plight of Myanmar Rohingyas exposes Southeast Asia’s disjointed policies and fragile human rights protections.
					</p>
				</div>
					</div>

		<div class="article-main-image">
			<img class="article-main-image-img" src="https://www.lowyinstitute.org/sites/default/files/styles/interpreter_article_image/public/2022-11/Rohingya%20headband%20comp.jpg?itok=tYR-jdqH" alt="A Rohingya refugee living in Malaysia wears a headband reading &quot;Save Rohingya&quot; during a protest in Kuala Lumpur in 2017 (Mohd Rasfan/AFP via Getty Images)">
              <div class="article-save-btn">
          
